  "What is cash flow analysis in personal finance?": "",
  "Only tracking income amounts, at least according to standard theory": "",
  "Counting the physical cash in your wallet, particularly in the context of analysis": "",
  "Measuring your total net worth when considering all relevant analysis factors": "",
  "Tracking when money comes in and goes out during a period to understand timing and avoid overdrafts": "",
  "Cash flow analysis examines when money enters and leaves your accounts. Understanding timing -- such as being paid on the 1st and 15th but having bills due throughout the month -- helps prevent overdrafts and late payments.": "",
  "What is the savings rate?": "",
  "The rate at which prices increase over time": "",
  "The speed at which you pay off debt": "",
  "The interest rate earned on a savings account": "",
  "The percentage of income that is saved rather than spent, calculated as savings divided by income": "",
  "The savings rate is a key financial metric calculated by dividing the amount saved by total income. A 20% savings rate on $50,000 income means saving $10,000 per year.": "",
  "What is an expense leak?": "",
